derivation: from G4253 (προέρχομαι) and G2064 (προέρχομαι) (including its alternate);
kjv_def: go before (farther, forward), outgo, pass on
strongs_def: to go onward, precede (in place or time)
outline:
1. to go forward, go on
  2. to go before
    1. to go before, precede
    2. to go before, in the advance of another
